.TH F00-LS 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00-ls \- list directory contents (f00 suite)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00-ls
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
List information about FILEs (the current directory by default).
Part of the
.B f00
coreutils replacement suite (pure assembly).
.PP
Default mode is
.B modern
(color, icons on a TTY, optional git).
.B --core
selects strict GNU coreutils
.B ls
compatible output.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-all\fR
do not ignore entries starting with .
.TP
\fB\-l\fR
use a long listing format
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-human\-readable\fR
with \-l and \-s, print sizes like 1K 234M 2G
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR[=\fIWHEN\fR]
colorize the output; WHEN is auto, always, or never
.PP
See
.B f00-ls --help
for the full coreutils-compatible flag list.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils-compatible output (no icons/git/json defaults)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-core\fR
force modern mode even when stdout is not a TTY
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
detailed JSON listing (pretty and colored on a TTY)
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
detailed CSV listing
.TP
\fB\-\-tree\fR
tree view
.TP
\fB\-\-git\fR
annotate with git status
.TP
\fB\-\-icons\fR[=\fIWHEN\fR]
Nerd Font icons
.TP
\fB\-\-browse\fR
interactive dual-pane browser
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ls (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
https://f00.sh
